title: 2020 United States elections
added: Michael McDonald projects that over 160 million people voted in the 2020 elections, compared to a turnout of approximately 137 million in the 2016 presidential election. McDonald projects that about 67% of the [[Voter turnout in the United States presidential elections|voting eligible population]] voted in 2020, which would be the highest rate of voter participation since the [[1900 United States elections|1900 election]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Lauter |first1=David |last2=Hook |first2=Janet |title=Americans broke a 120-year-old turnout record — and are more divided than ever |url=https://www.latimes.com/politics/story/2020-11-04/2020-election-trump-biden-count-analysis |publisher=LA Times |date=November 4, 2020}}</ref>
